headline: Carla McDonnell, 16, from Ireland, wins NFTE’s 2025 World Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge
summary: More than $7,000 in prizes awarded to top three student ventures from around the world NFTE World Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge Champion Carla McDonnell from Foróige in Ireland took first place in the Nov. 20 World Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge with her business idea Vax Chill. nfte.com. 2025 NFTE World Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge Finalists Judges pose with youth whose business ideas won top recognition at the 2025 NFTE World Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge.
